() Tj
T*
(Interactive development:) Tj
T*
(- `codex`) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Automated one-shot runs:) Tj
T*
(- `codex exec "your task"`) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Higher-autonomy automation:) Tj
T*
(- `codex exec --full-auto "your task"`) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Goal: choose interactivity level based on risk and CI context.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Step E: Add a loop for safe execution) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Recommended loop:) Tj
T*
(1. Read constraints \(`AGENTS.md`, program docs\)) Tj
T*
(2. Inspect relevant files only) Tj
T*
(3. Make minimal scoped edits) Tj
T*
(4. Run validators \(`build`, project scripts, policy checks\)) Tj
T*
(5. Summarize exact outcomes and next steps) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Goal: maintain velocity without widening blast radius.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 3\) App-level API agent workflow \(product integration\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Step A: Use Responses API as the agent core) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Use Responses API for stateful, tool-using workflows.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Step B: Select coding-capable model) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(For coding-focused flows, use a coding-capable model \(for example `gpt-5-codex`\) according to) Tj
T*
(current model docs.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Step C: Add tools) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Implement tool calling for:) Tj
T*
(- internal functions \(CRUD, business actions\),) Tj
T*
(- retrieval/search,) Tj
T*
(- external MCP resources where needed.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Step D: Add orchestration and memory) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Track:) Tj
T*
(- conversation/session state,) Tj
T*
(- task state,) Tj
T*
(- tool outputs,) Tj
T*
(- retry/fallback policies.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
ET
endstream
